markets.title: Will James Walkinshaw win between 50% and 100% of votes in the 2025 Virginia's 11th congressional district special election?
markets.rules_primary: If the margin of victory for James Walkinshaw in the 2025 Virginia's 11th congressional district special election is between 50% and 100%, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The margin of victory is calculated based on the margin type specified. For percentage points: the difference between the candidate's vote share and their closest competitor's share. Positive margins indicate the candidate won, negative margins indicate they lost, and zero indicates a tie. For uncontested races, the margin is 100 percentage points or total votes cast. Write-in votes are aggregated as a single candidate if not individually reported. Only certified results are used for resolution. If the election is cancelled, postponed beyond expiration, or no certified results are available, all markets resolve to No. Recounts that change the certified margin before expiration use the most recent certified results.
markets.early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if certified election results are published.
